cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with a fundamental problem in computational geometry, specifically the Maximum Weight Independent Set of Polygons problem. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves approximation algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The use of a partitioning method and the handling of arbitrary angles of polygons suggest cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of geometric intersection graphs, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible sub-category.
